# CSS architecture

See [front/sub.md](mdc:front/sub.md) and [AGENTS.md](mdc:AGENTS.md).

| File | Holds |
|------|--------|
| `front/tailwind.config.js` | Design tokens (colors, fonts, spacing from Publish) |
| `front/src/public/css/common.css` | Tailwind import, body, shared components (e.g. footer) |
| `front/src/public/css/<page>.css` | Page-only classes (e.g. login-card) |

## Rules

- If the same declaration appears on 2+ pages → move to `common.css`
- Page CSS should not redefine global tokens (colors, font stacks, base spacing)
- Avoid `!important` unless fixing third-party export junk; remove after refactor
- Prefer class selectors over deep element chains from exported HTML

## Publish HTML conversion

1. Extract shared rules first → `common.css`
2. Leave page-specific rules in `<Page>.css`
3. Replace inline `style=""` with classes when repeated twice or more
